Jamaica Avenue, north side, between 127th and 130th Streets, showing the Dow Ditmars House, built before the Revolution. Dow Ditmars; son of John Ditmars, died about 1755. The house was occupied by Pat Cary in 1860; by Mrs O'Connor in 1891; by Dominicus Vandeveer in 1902; Adikes was the owner in 1923. The house was demolished in late 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster

Jamaica Avenue, north side, between 127th and 130th Streets, showing the Dow Ditmars house. Some occupants of this property were P. Cary 1860 and Mrs. L.G. Blinck in 1872. Other owners were Dominicus Vanderveer in 1881, and Mrs. O'Conner in 1891. It was sold in 1891 and one Adikes was the owner in 1922. The house was demolished in October 1928. No. 3 looks east and shows the Long Island Railroad embankment in the background. In View No. 4 the B.M.T. Elevated structure is seen towering over Jamaica Avenue.
